The paper discusses a language for specifying and running unit tests on ASP programs, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). ASP is a declarative logic programming formalism, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the implementation of the testing language in ASPIDE, which is a comprehensive IDE for ASP, indicating a focus on software tools and software development (cs.SW). Finally, the paper discusses the entire life-cycle of ASP development, which includes program composition, testing, debugging, profiling, solver execution configuration, and output-handling, suggesting a connection to logic in computer science (cs.LO).
